This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) because it proposes a novel algorithm that learns controllable features for enhanced generalization and fast task inference. It also uses reinforcement learning techniques to train agents on the Atari suite. Additionally, it could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) because it deals with training agents to perform tasks. Computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a possible sub-category since the Atari games involve visual input. Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY) because it deals with controlling the behavior of agents in a Markov decision process.
